From 5e656be7e8c6504c2c8e9bfc4414411ef4f90feb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vignesh C <vignc@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 19 Aug 2025 10:38:11 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:CP wifi:ath12k: Fix bridge vdev channel context
 selection during monitor vdev startup

In UD, monitor vdev is brought up independently, regardless of
AP vdev presence. This differs from previous design, where monitor
vdev (MLO monitor) was tagged along with the first AP vdev during
startup. If no AP vdev existed, monitor vdev would not be created
or started, ensuring synchronized context.

Currently, when a monitor vdev is started on 6GHz and AP MLD is added
with 2GHz followed by 6GHz vdev, the bridge logic identifies the need
for bridging and proceeds to create bridge vdevs on 5GHz and 6GHz.

During bridge vdev creation, the channel context is determined by
checking if any arvif exists on the radio with a defined channel
context

However, since arvif->chanctx is not assigned during monitor vdev
startup, this logic returns NULL, causing the bridge vdev to default
to a home channel. This results in two home channel configurations,
which is unintended and can lead to channel mismatches.

Fix this by assigning arvif->chanctx after successful monitor vdev
start.

Patch-dependency:
ath12k/0327-02-wifi-ath12k-n-link-mlo-bridge-vdev-create-start.patch

Signed-off-by: Vignesh C <vignc@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
index f40786f..e9b3667 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
@@ -17779,6 +17779,9 @@ ath12k_mac_assign_vif_chanctx_handle(struct ieee80211_hw *hw,
 			goto out;
 		}
 
+		if (ctx)
+			memcpy(&arvif->chanctx, ctx, sizeof(*ctx));
+
 		arvif->is_started = true;
 		goto out;
 	}
